column5: I'm 1 species off for the avid angler award on the ofah awards thing... i guess crappie and rockbass count as one... but i already got the walleye, pike and bass down... i guess i need to hook into a musky, whitefish or salmon before its too late... anyone got some tips before the year end and before i gotta store away my boat to where i can hook into some? i'm thinking of BOQ again.. since they got some giant eyes at the moment and i heard there is a mix of everything.. i guess thats my best chance is there...  woot  kevin
Simcoe has whitefish   But I wouldnt try it just yet,LOL  Good luck Kevin

i know there is whitefish during the hardwater season that are easy to get... not too sure right now.. i haven't been there in a while.. how about the smallies right now? how they are doing around the keswick area? i could try and head out there.. .. since my entry was a largie...
Why not try for the mighty GOBY! That'll get ya the last species. (No please don't hit me)
